FBIS3-35529 "drnes038dd_94015" FBIS-NES-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 Palestinian Affairs Palestinian Leaders Comments on Hebron Mosque Attack PLO Lisbon Envoy Wants Settlers Out LD2502111894 Lisbon Radio Renascenca in Portuguese to Europe 0900 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502111894 Lisbon Radio Renascenca Language: Portuguese Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The toll of this morning's massacre in the West Bank has already risen to 49. [passage omitted] Yasir 'Arafat has requested an urgent meeting of the UN Security Council. In Lisbon, PLO representative 'Isam al-Baysusu has echoed 'Arafat's stance and said that responsibility for the massacre must be apportioned in full to the Israeli state: [Begin al-Baysusu recording] This is the Israeli Government's problem. Whether or not it was perpetrated by a fanatic, as far as we are concerned this was a crime, a massacre, and the responsibility lies fully at the Israeli Government's door, because it is the Israeli Government that sets up Israeli settlements on Palestinian territories. [end recording] [passage omitted] [Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese in a similar report at 0900 GMT on 25 February carries the following recording remarks by al-Baysusu: "The peace negotiations are really in danger, because we agreed to postpone negotiating on the problem of the Israeli settlements for two years, and now this means that we must discuss the problem of the settlements immediately. They must all leave Palestine."]
